-- Shares in UK banks open higher after PRA stress test passes
-- 
-- Tue Dec 16, 2014 03:11AM EST
-- None



LONDON, Dec 16 (Reuters) - Shares in Britain's biggest banks were higher in early trading after they passed the first of a new annual health check by the Bank of England. [ID:nL6N0U00OW]

The FTSE 350 Banks Index <.FTNMX.> was up 0.8 percent at 0808 GMT. Shares in Barclays were up 1.3 percent with HSBC up 0.9 percent. State-backed Royal Bank of Scotland <RBS.L> and Lloyds Banking Group <LLOY.L>, which had the weakest passes, were both up by 0.5 percent.